{"title": "Red Flower: Poems Written in War Time", "description": "These are verses that came to me in this dreadful war time amid the cares and labors of a heavy task.<br></br>\n\nTwo of the poems, \"A Scrap of Paper\" and \"Stand Fast,\" were written in 1914 and bore the signature Civis Americanus\u2014the use of my own name at the time being impossible. Two others, \"Lights Out\" and \"Remarks about Kings,\" were read for me by Robert Underwood Johnson at the meeting of the American Academy in Boston, November, 1915, at which I was unable to be present.<br></br>\n\nThe rest of the verses were printed after I had resigned my diplomatic post and was free to say what I thought and felt, without reserve.<br></br>\n\nThe \"Interludes in Holland\" are thoughts of the peaceful things that will abide for all the world after we have won this war against war.<br></br>\n\nSYLVANORA, October 1, 1917. - Summary by  Henry Van Dyke", "duration": 2665, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "836", "name": "Henry van Dyke"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/red_flower_1602_librivox/red_flower_1602.jpg", "copyright_year": "1917", "genres": ["Poetry"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Crln Yldz Ksr"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Crln Yldz Ksr"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Sonia"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Red Flower", "readers": [7785], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/red_flower_1602_librivox/redflower_01_vandyke_64kb.mp3", "duration": 124}, {"section": 2, "title": "A Scrap of Paper", "readers": [7785], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/red_flower_1602_librivox/redflower_02_vandyke_64kb.mp3", "duration": 87}, {"section": 3, "title": "Stand Fast", "readers": [10508], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/red_flower_1602_librivox/redflower_03_vandyke_64kb.mp3", "duration": 89}, {"section": 4, "title": "Lights Out", "readers": [10573], "path": "h